.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX shell that reads commands from standard input and executes them.
It supports basic command execution, arguments, PATH handling, and built-in commands
like
.B exit
and
.B env.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode:
.B ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
dir1 dir2 file1
($) exit
.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.SH AUTHOR
Written by [Your Name].
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh(1),
.BR execve(2),
.BR fork(2)
